The film stars Kiera Allen as disabled teenager Chloe Sherman, who begins to suspect that her mother, Diane (Sarah Paulson), has been keeping a dark secret about her upbringing. Chloe begins to hyperventilate before Diane runs in and sedates her to take her home. * Sarah Paulson as Diane Sherman, Chloe's mother. In November 2018, Ohanian revealed that *Run* includes intentional references "Easter egg (media)") to his previous film *Searching "Searching (film)")*, while also stating that the latter has connections to the prior as well. data.snippet: Use your left and right arrow keys to control the runner. Use the space key to jump. ## Run - Skill Building Game. Students control a character running through a series of tunnels suspended in space. They think ahead and adapt quickly to changes in the tunnel environment to successfully complete each level. * **Skills Developed:** quick decision-making, spatial awareness, adaptability, and motor skills. ISTE Standards for Computational Thinking - foster problem solving by experimenting with different approaches to jump and move through the tunnels and adjusting strategies to succeed. Brain Break - fast-paced gameplay and focus on timing and precision make this game a fun way for students to refresh their focus while honing problem-solving and reaction skills. The film stars Kiera Allen as disabled teenager Chloe Sherman, who begins to suspect that her mother, Diane (Sarah Paulson), has been keeping a dark secret about her upbringing. Chloe begins to hyperventilate before Diane runs in and sedates her to take her home. * Sarah Paulson as Diane Sherman, Chloe's mother. In November 2018, Ohanian revealed that *Run* includes intentional references "Easter egg (media)") to his previous film *Searching "Searching (film)")*, while also stating that the latter has connections to the prior as well.
